    <item>
      <title>Feeds I Love</title>
      <link>http://localhost:42853/posts/20260424t113727--feeds-i-love__blog_rss/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 11:37:00 -0500</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:42853/posts/20260424t113727--feeds-i-love__blog_rss/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This is a list of my favorite RSS feeds and blogs, and I plan to update it regularly for&#xA;both myself and for others.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A complete list of my feeds/blogs/sites will be available on &lt;a href=&#34;https://matthew-kennedy.com/links&#34;&gt;my links page&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;friends&#34;&gt;Friends&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://joshuablais.com/feed.xml&#34;&gt;Joshua Blais&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linuxmaxxing.com/index.xml&#34;&gt;Scotty&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://cashmere.rs/feed.xml&#34;&gt;cashmere&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://xn--gckvb8fzb.com/index.xml&#34;&gt;Marius&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://joshtronic.com/atom.xml&#34;&gt;Josh Sherman&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://inv.thepixora.com/feed/channel/UCwjc4WMqQWmQCUXt3XpZJ9A&#34;&gt;Lindon Slaght&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;reading&#34;&gt;Reading&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://irreal.org/blog/?feed=rss2&#34;&gt;Irreal&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://emacsredux.com/atom.xml&#34;&gt;Emacs Redux (Bozhidar Batsov)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://protesilaos.com/master.xml&#34;&gt;Protesilaos&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://sachachua.com/blog/category/emacs/feed/&#34;&gt;Sacha Chua&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://jacobwsmith.xyz/feed.xml&#34;&gt;Jacob Smith&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://christiantietze.de/feed.atom&#34;&gt;Christian Tietze&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;watching&#34;&gt;Watching&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve moved all YouTube feeds to &lt;a href=&#34;https://invidious.io/&#34;&gt;Invidious&lt;/a&gt;, as the YouTube RSS feeds seem to be&#xA;on their last legs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Technical exhaustion and the downfall of systemd</title>
      <link>http://localhost:42853/posts/20260320t173728--technical-exhaustion-and-the-downfall-of-systemd__ageverification_linux_systemd/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 20 Mar 2026 17:37:00 -0500</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:42853/posts/20260320t173728--technical-exhaustion-and-the-downfall-of-systemd__ageverification_linux_systemd/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I opened &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/skeeto/elfeed&#34;&gt;Elfeed&lt;/a&gt; (the best RSS reader) to see this post&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://itsfoss.com/news/systemd-age-verification/&#34;&gt;https://itsfoss.com/news/systemd-age-verification/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I was struck by many thoughts and emotions, mainly those of &amp;ldquo;What the heck?&amp;rdquo; and a general feeling of frustration.&#xA;Amongst all of this, I also felt something that has become all to familiar to me in this era in which we live: mental exhaustion.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;These days, it seems like we live in a never-ending nightmare for privacy and our basic rights to live our lives in peace.&#xA;This age verification garbage is just the next step in the march towards complete monitoring (think &lt;a href=&#34;https://openlibrary.org/works/OL1168083W/Nineteen_Eighty-Four?edition=key%3A/books/OL3174961M&#34;&gt;1984&lt;/a&gt;, but with a nice coat of &amp;ldquo;Think of the children!&amp;rdquo;).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>How to Learn Programming Languages</title>
      <link>http://localhost:42853/posts/20260129t104751--how-to-learn-programming-languages__blog_programming_video/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 29 Jan 2026 10:47:00 -0600</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:42853/posts/20260129t104751--how-to-learn-programming-languages__blog_programming_video/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Source: &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uqpr8FFS9U0&#34;&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uqpr8FFS9U0&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;abstract&#34;&gt;Abstract&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The brain throws away information it deems as useless or unimportant.&#xA;To properly learn a language, we must train our brain to see it as useful&#xA;information by immediately putting it into practice, and using it to fulfill&#xA;a need we have, whether that be a gap in our workflow, or a simple little tool&#xA;that makes a task just that &lt;em&gt;little&lt;/em&gt; bit faster.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;notes&#34;&gt;Notes&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Oglo recommends a 4-step process:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
