    <item>
      <title>Technology: Hurting or Helping?</title>
      <link>http://localhost:42853/posts/20260110t190340--technology-hurting-or-helping__equip_lesson_meta_technology/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 10 Jan 2026 19:03:00 -0600</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:42853/posts/20260110t190340--technology-hurting-or-helping__equip_lesson_meta_technology/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;initium&#34;&gt;Initium&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Technology is everywhere in our daily lives.&#xA;At work and school, computers have become an essential part of how we work, to&#xA;the point that the vast majority of tasks can&amp;rsquo;t be done away from a screen.&#xA;At home, we spend our free time on our phones, computers, or TVs, seeking an&#xA;escape from the struggles of daily life, and the horrifying notion of being&#xA;alone with our own thoughts.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
